The paper focuses on the problem of public Bayesian persuasion, which involves a sender strategically providing information to multiple receivers to influence their behavior. This problem is studied in the context of game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.AI), and involves computational complexity analysis (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms (cs.LG) for solving the problem.
